n Yogesh Kumar Bhattarai, Minister for Health and Population Bhanu Bhakta Dhakal and Minister for Labour, Employment and Social Security Rameshwor Raya as well as the office-bearers of the CCMC had collected the recommendations furnished by the representatives of the service providers.\n\nMeanwhile, it was said that the government could enforce a lockdown yet again if the number of active infection cases surpasses 25,000.\n\nCurrently, the country records 17,414 active cases of COVID-19. The total number of COVID-19 cases in the country stands at 67,804.","title":"DPM Pokhrel directs CCMC for preparing effective strategy - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/24/129909/","video":[]}
